1
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:14,033
Meet my father.

2
00:00:14,133 --> 00:00:16,267
I know him, son.
He's an employee of mine.

3
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,800
We'll just be outside
so you two can talk.

4
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:21,300
I know that familiar feeling.

5
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:23,600
The feeling of almost
losing your child.

6
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,433
The moment I saw Enzo in danger,

7
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:28,067
I didn't think twice.

8
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:31,867
I did what needed to be done.

9
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:34,200
Sir, Enzo's like family to me.

10
00:00:34,933 --> 00:00:36,767
- Roldan?
- What's the update?

11
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:37,900
It's done.

12
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:41,767
Their broken bones have
turned to ashes by now.

13
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:43,067
Good.

14
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:49,767
Chloe--

15
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,300
Who are you looking for?

16
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:53,733
I just thought I saw someone.

17
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,167
- Come on.
- Let's go.

18
00:00:58,167 --> 00:00:59,767
I feel that
there's some distance

19
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:02,000
between Enzo and his dad.

20
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:05,400
You told me that
someone saved Enzo.

21
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,433
Well, I was hoping to meet them.

22
00:01:08,567 --> 00:01:10,800
To thank them personally,
you know.

23
00:01:10,967 --> 00:01:12,633
Do you know what
his room number is?

24
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:13,833
He's currently resting.

25
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,600
Besides, they already
thanked the guy.

26
00:01:16,867 --> 00:01:18,333
Let's go, honey.

27
00:01:20,633 --> 00:01:21,467
- Mama?
- Hmm?
What's the matter?

28
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:24,000
You look like
you've seen a ghost.

29
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:25,100
It's nothing.

30
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:27,633
The doctor has signed
your discharge papers.

31
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:29,100
You're free to go.

32
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:31,500
- Oh, thank goodness.
- Yay!

33
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:33,767
We know they're operating
on a large scale.

34
00:01:33,867 --> 00:01:37,000
Surely, there's a much more
powerful figure behind all this.

35
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:38,833
So even if they're taken
out of the picture,

36
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,467
it won't be considered
a major loss.

37
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:42,467
This will only work
in their favor.

38
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:46,000
Because we wouldn't know
who would replace them.

39
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:48,067
Look, I understand the stakes.

40
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:50,500
But I have to finish my mission.

41
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:53,833
I need to uncover every dirty
little secret they're hiding.

42
00:01:54,567 --> 00:01:56,867
How long has it been
since your son left?

43
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:59,167
It's been six months, sir.

44
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:02,333
He used to update me
every now and then.

45
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:04,733
And how many weeks has it been
since you two last talked?

46
00:02:04,867 --> 00:02:06,567
Three weeks, sir.

47
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:10,000
I have a bad feeling about this.

48
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,733
This isn't like him at all.

49
00:02:16,933 --> 00:02:23,767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:42,700
[JOHNNY] Come here.

51
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,700
[WOMAN SNIFFLES]

52
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:46,533
I'm not trying to make you
worry even more,

53
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:50,567
but there's been a significant
spike in kidnappings lately.

54
00:02:50,733 --> 00:02:51,933
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:54,800
None of these people were
ever seen again

56
00:02:54,933 --> 00:02:57,633
after accepting a job offer.

57
00:02:57,767 --> 00:02:59,900
As you can see,

58
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:02,733
some of the men
worked as programmers.

59
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,433
And the women
were usually models.

60
00:03:07,567 --> 00:03:09,233
We suspect that they have
all become victims

61
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,733
of human trafficking.

62
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,433
[WOMAN SOBS]
My goodness.

63
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,867
My son...

64
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:20,400
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

65
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,267
But don't worry, ma'am.

66
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:27,567
I'm going to help you
find your son, okay?

67
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:30,400
Thank you so much, sir.

68
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:35,967
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,933
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

70
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,433
I'd better not see any slackers!

71
00:03:51,433 --> 00:03:53,267
Fail to meet your quota

72
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:56,000
and the boss will make you
regret it.

73
00:03:56,167 --> 00:03:59,300
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,467
[INHALES SHARPLY]

75
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:02,967
Better work hard, kid.

76
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:05,933
Or else it's another round
of beating for you.

77
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:07,800
Understood, sir.

78
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,700
Now what the heck
are you looking at?

79
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:13,467
Get back to work!

80
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:21,633
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

81
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:27,900
[SLAPS]

82
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:30,400
Damn it, focus!

83
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:36,867
How will you meet your quota
at that pace?

84
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:38,900
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

85
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:40,733
[INAUDIBLE]

86
00:04:49,367 --> 00:04:51,200
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

87
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:52,300
[GIRL 1] Place your bets!

88
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,000
[BELL RINGING]

89
00:04:54,167 --> 00:04:55,133
Good luck!

90
00:04:55,233 --> 00:05:02,233
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:10,200
[GIRL 2]
Players, place your bets.

92
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,367
Good luck!

93
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:14,433
[GIRL 3] Player wins!

94
00:05:15,233 --> 00:05:16,667
- Place your bets!
- Place your bets!

95
00:05:16,767 --> 00:05:17,867
Let's go!

96
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:19,700
[SINISTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

97
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,933
- Player wins!
- Good luck, players!

98
00:05:22,067 --> 00:05:23,067
Place your bets!

99
00:05:23,233 --> 00:05:24,700
Banker wins!

100
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,400
Players, place your...

101
00:05:28,267 --> 00:05:31,000
[MAEL] Dude, you should've told
 me you were coming to work.

102
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,333
I would've given you a ride.

103
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:33,933
You sound like my mom, dude.

104
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,400
I'm okay.

105
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:36,767
I've got myself covered.

106
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,733
I can't afford more delays
to my plans.

107
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:40,800
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:41,767
Okay, then.

109
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:43,767
Just call me if something
comes up.

110
00:05:52,267 --> 00:05:53,733
Do you know who I am?

111
00:05:54,967 --> 00:05:56,400
You're...

112
00:05:57,133 --> 00:05:58,700
Gen. Ramirez.

113
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,100
The Scam Buster.

114
00:06:00,267 --> 00:06:03,400
And you're Samuel Trinidad.

115
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:06,133
Son of a scammer.

116
00:06:06,267 --> 00:06:11,433
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

117
00:06:11,633 --> 00:06:13,767
What can I do for you?

118
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:15,333
Oh, don't worry.

119
00:06:15,467 --> 00:06:16,767
This is going to be quick.

120
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:18,767
Everything will be fine.

121
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:20,833
As long as you tell me
the truth, that is.

122
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:25,300
We won't have any issues because
I didn't do anything wrong.

123
00:06:27,767 --> 00:06:28,800
You know,

124
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:31,833
back when your father
was still alive,

125
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:37,600
people saw him coming in and out
of this very building.

126
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:39,233
What was he doing here?

127
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,767
This is the first time
I'm hearing about it.

129
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,633
Really?

130
00:06:45,333 --> 00:06:49,633
It just seems a little
too coincidental.

131
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:54,833
You showing up here
after he died.

132
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:58,800
Actually, I've heard
one more thing.

133
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:02,267
That they recruited you
to work for them.

134
00:07:02,367 --> 00:07:04,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:05,333
Now, I...

136
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,933
I was just wondering.

137
00:07:09,067 --> 00:07:12,533
Why would they hire
the son of a scammer?

138
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:17,667
What use are you to them?

139
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:22,000
Perhaps the better question is,

140
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

141
00:07:23,367 --> 00:07:26,833
are you now continuing
whatever role

142
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,833
your father started with them?

143
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:40,467
Sir, if you want to know
why they recruited me,

144
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:43,467
maybe you should personally
ask my boss instead.

145
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:46,500
Only he can give you
the answer you're looking for.

146
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:53,433
What I'm offering you is
a chance for redemption, kid.

148
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,533
Help me.

149
00:07:57,567 --> 00:07:59,667
Clean your name.

150
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:02,700
What I'm offering you...

151
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:07,100
is a chance for a fresh start.

152
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:10,733
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

153
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:13,867
Sir, I took a bullet
just the other day.

154
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:15,733
I almost died.

155
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:17,667
But I didn't.

156
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,400
I'm still with my family.

157
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,133
I can still go to work.

158
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:25,067
Sir, for me...

159
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:29,067
that's a fresh start.

160
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:30,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

161
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:32,733
Thanks for the offer, though.

162
00:08:36,067 --> 00:08:39,433
I see you're not easily
intimidated, Samuel.

163
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:47,400
You're a very interesting man.

164
00:08:47,567 --> 00:08:54,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:08:54,467 --> 00:09:01,567
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:09,133
[APPLAUSE]

167
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:16,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

168
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:27,800
Welcome back, Samuel.

169
00:09:30,067 --> 00:09:31,167
Thank you, sir.

170
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:33,967
[ROLDAN]
Now, we are not just...

171
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:36,267
welcoming a colleague.

172
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:39,300
We are celebrating Samuel.

173
00:09:39,467 --> 00:09:40,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:45,833
A loyal, brave, and kind man.

175
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:47,633
Samuel,

176
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:51,100
you didn't just risk your life
for someone.

177
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,633
You risked your life for my son.

178
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:58,833
And I will be forever grateful
to you.

179
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:05,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:09,000
Thank you, sir, for those, uh...

181
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:10,233
kind words.

182
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:14,333
Enzo is a nice kid,

183
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:17,033
and he is a good friend
to my sister.

184
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:22,233
And he helped me
when my son was kidnapped.

185
00:10:22,367 --> 00:10:25,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

186
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:27,167
[ROLDAN BREATHES DEEPLY]

187
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,967
I'll never forget that.

188
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:31,067
Samuel.

189
00:10:32,267 --> 00:10:37,067
I can only hope to repay
your good deed someday.

190
00:10:40,733 --> 00:10:42,200
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,400
That's enough talking.

192
00:10:43,567 --> 00:10:45,100
Come on, let's have a toast.

193
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:46,100
[GLASSES CLINK]

194
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:49,033
[APPLAUSE]

195
00:10:49,133 --> 00:10:50,933
- Cheers.
- Cheers!

196
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,333
[GLASSES CLINK]

197
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:53,833
- [CONFETTI POPS]
- [CHEERING]

198
00:10:53,933 --> 00:10:56,667
- Welcome back, Samuel!
- Welcome back, Samuel!

199
00:10:56,767 --> 00:10:59,167
- [WHOOPING, CLAPPING]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:02,000
[JACOB]
The food's waiting, everyone.

201
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:04,100
Eat up.

202
00:11:04,933 --> 00:11:05,867
Go.

203
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:13,233
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

204
00:11:17,933 --> 00:11:20,067
Samuel, is the party over?

205
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:21,600
Come in.

206
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:26,567
Sir, I'd like to...

207
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:30,600
- ...have a word.
- If this is about work,

208
00:11:30,767 --> 00:11:32,467
I told you to file for leave,

209
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,967
but you insisted on coming in.

210
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:35,933
It's not about work.

211
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:39,433
It's about...

212
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,133
Enzo.

213
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:45,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:47,333
What about my son?

215
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:50,133
What happened to him
is really serious.

216
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:54,000
Someone tried... to kill him.

217
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:59,400
Have the police found out
who's behind it yet?

218
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:02,000
Not yet.

219
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,333
But...

220
00:12:05,167 --> 00:12:08,767
I can't think of anyone
who could've done that to him.

221
00:12:08,867 --> 00:12:10,167
Besides...

222
00:12:11,033 --> 00:12:12,500
my son has no enemies.

223
00:12:12,633 --> 00:12:13,633
Maybe it's you.

224
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:15,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:17,000
Oh, um...

226
00:12:17,667 --> 00:12:19,333
I mean, sir, maybe...

227
00:12:20,133 --> 00:12:22,533
you have enemies.

228
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:24,367
Me?

229
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:27,000
I don't.

230
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,167
Okay.

231
00:12:31,733 --> 00:12:34,033
Sir, I... I...

232
00:12:34,167 --> 00:12:36,967
I just wanted to
voice out my concern,

233
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:41,600
so you could
protect your son, Enzo.

234
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:45,033
Obviously, I will do
my best to protect him,

235
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,533
but, sir, you are the one...

236
00:12:48,667 --> 00:12:51,033
with more resources.

237
00:12:51,167 --> 00:12:54,067
Why the sudden concern
about my son?

238
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:58,233
Well, sir, if there's
one thing about me,

239
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:01,800
it's that I know

240
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:04,000
how to be grateful.

241
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:07,800
You and Enzo helped me

242
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:11,233
at a time when
I needed it the most,

243
00:13:11,367 --> 00:13:14,367
even when you didn't have to.

244
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:15,567
Family.

245
00:13:16,667 --> 00:13:20,400
I consider you family, sir.

246
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:24,267
For now...

247
00:13:26,967 --> 00:13:28,567
leave my son alone.

248
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:31,700
I can take care of my son.

249
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:36,033
Yes, sir. Okay.

250
00:13:36,133 --> 00:13:43,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:13:57,167 --> 00:13:59,867
- I'd like some dessert.
- Hey, Danny!

252
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,867
You're just in time.

253
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,067
Everyone, this is Danny,

254
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:07,433
one of Mike Trinidad's
scam victims.

255
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:11,567
Is he your new supplier
of rice cakes?

256
00:14:12,633 --> 00:14:14,533
- They look delicious.
- [DANNY] They are, ma'am.

257
00:14:14,667 --> 00:14:16,533
Alright, I'll take one.

258
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:18,467
- Sure, ma'am.
- [WOMAN 1] Me too.

259
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,800
[WOMAN 2]
Us too. Put it on tab.

260
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:22,433
I think I like this one too.

261
00:14:22,567 --> 00:14:24,800
You're quite admirable, mister.

262
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:30,033
You keep going, even after
all that you've been through.

263
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,167
Truth is, ma'am,

264
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:35,433
when the vehicle I used
for my trips was taken

265
00:14:35,533 --> 00:14:38,100
and the loan sharks
began going after me,

266
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:40,500
I thought of giving up.

267
00:14:40,667 --> 00:14:44,933
But I told myself I can't,
my family needs me.

268
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:48,333
Why don't you join
our support group?

269
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:50,067
- Yes, join us.
- Join us.

270
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:53,433
It'll help you feel
you're not facing this alone.

271
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:56,667
Oh, alright. I...

272
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:57,633
I'll stay next time.

273
00:14:57,767 --> 00:15:01,333
I just need to
deliver these rice cakes.

274
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,767
Okay, Mister Danny.
Please take care.

275
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:05,933
Thank you. I'll be off now.

276
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:07,433
Thank you.

277
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:10,700
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
- These look good.

278
00:15:10,867 --> 00:15:12,267
Wh-What's the problem, Danny?

279
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:15,100
The loan shark I owe
is right outside.

280
00:15:15,233 --> 00:15:21,300
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,200
You think you can hide from us?

282
00:15:23,333 --> 00:15:24,533
- [LOAN SHARK GRUNTS]
- [PEOPLE EXCLAIM]

283
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:26,633
I swear I'll pay.
That's why I'm work--

284
00:15:26,733 --> 00:15:28,600
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [PEOPLE EXCLAIM] Oh gosh!

285
00:15:28,733 --> 00:15:30,200
Hey, what are you doing?!

286
00:15:30,367 --> 00:15:32,000
Stay out of our business.

287
00:15:32,133 --> 00:15:34,200
How can we stay out of it?

288
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,233
You're beating up our colleague!

289
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,300
[WOMEN GASP]

290
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:42,667
- [WOMEN SCREAM]
- [CLAMORING]

291
00:15:42,767 --> 00:15:43,900
Stop it! Stop it!

292
00:15:44,067 --> 00:15:45,200
[WOMEN SCREAM]

293
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:48,200
- Let go of him!
- Stay out of this!

294
00:15:49,267 --> 00:15:52,367
[PLATES CLATTERING]

295
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,733
Stop it!

296
00:15:58,033 --> 00:16:01,167
[CLAMORING, SCREAMING CONTINUE]

297
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:02,400
[WOMAN 3] Please stop!

298
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:04,967
You got lucky
because you found allies!

299
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:08,133
Go ahead! Attack us!

300
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,767
You'll see
who you're dealing with!

301
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:12,733
Watch your back, Danny.
We're coming back for you!

302
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,600
- Your time will come.
- Go away!

303
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,100
[PANTING]

304
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:20,400
Oh my god.

305
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:22,933
I'm so sorry.

306
00:16:23,067 --> 00:16:24,733
I got you involved.

307
00:16:25,867 --> 00:16:28,533
Don't worry about it, Danny.

308
00:16:28,633 --> 00:16:30,700
What matters is we're all
here for each other.

309
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:31,933
We stick together!

310
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:33,867
- That's right.
- We're all in this.

311
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:37,700
Thank you. Thank you.

312
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,267
Are you hurt?

313
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,433
My gosh. Let him sit.

314
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:43,533
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:47,533
Honestly, man,
I'm scared about your plan.

316
00:16:48,233 --> 00:16:49,967
Are you sure about that?

317
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:52,367
This is the only way I know

318
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:56,200
to get solid evidence
against them.

319
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:00,633
Anyway, we're right behind you.
We won't abandon you.

320
00:17:00,767 --> 00:17:02,300
[ISMAEL] Behind you,

321
00:17:02,433 --> 00:17:05,800
in front of you, beside you,
we'll be there for you.

322
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,300
Thank you.

323
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,967
But you don't need to worry.

324
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:13,967
There are people helping me.

325
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,467
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

326
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:21,767
[BROODING MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:17:22,467 --> 00:17:24,767
"Everything's set."

328
00:17:28,767 --> 00:17:30,267
I bought your favorite.

329
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:33,400
It's been a while
since we ate together.

330
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:39,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

331
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:43,767
Uh... It's small but cozy.

332
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:49,633
[CHUCKLES]

333
00:17:50,467 --> 00:17:51,633
Nice!

334
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:57,000
Your car and this condo unit
that you're renting...

335
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,833
all came from your hard work
and effort.

336
00:18:02,967 --> 00:18:05,033
I bet if your mom
were still here...

337
00:18:05,967 --> 00:18:07,300
she would be
proud of you.

338
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:12,667
Thank you.

339
00:18:13,367 --> 00:18:14,300
[CHUCKLES]

340
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:20,000
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

341
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:21,167
You know...

342
00:18:22,533 --> 00:18:24,333
you can always ask
for my help.

343
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,200
I know that
I'm always busy.

344
00:18:28,067 --> 00:18:31,033
But I'll forever
carry the guilt...

345
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:36,000
of not being around
when your mom died.

346
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:39,133
For that, I'm sorry.

347
00:18:41,567 --> 00:18:43,800
Don't worry, son.
I'll make it up to you.

348
00:18:45,267 --> 00:18:46,200
Mark my word.

349
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:49,867
Okay.

350
00:18:51,067 --> 00:18:52,533
I'll just prepare the food.

351
00:18:52,667 --> 00:18:56,567
[PHONE RINGING]

352
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:58,767
Agnes.

353
00:18:58,933 --> 00:19:01,733
Uh, sir... Is this a good time?

354
00:19:01,867 --> 00:19:04,200
Uh, no. But go ahead.
What's the problem?

355
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:05,500
Uh, sir...

356
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,067
We received
a mission order

357
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:09,900
from the National
Revenue Authority.

358
00:19:10,033 --> 00:19:14,500
They're conducting an audit
on Oriental Ridge Estates.

359
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:17,000
What?! An audit?!

360
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:18,000
When?

361
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:20,500
They said they'll start
tomorrow, sir.

362
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:22,933
Alright. I'll talk to Jacob.

363
00:19:24,033 --> 00:19:25,100
Okay, sir.

364
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,767
I have to go. Something came up
at work.

365
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:32,767
[DOOR OPENS]

366
00:19:34,267 --> 00:19:35,133
[DOOR CLOSES]

367
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:38,267
Maybe next time.

368
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:45,200
Roldan, these company books...

369
00:19:46,467 --> 00:19:48,567
are questionable.

370
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:50,467
They all have discrepancies.

371
00:19:50,633 --> 00:19:52,400
We'll get in trouble
if we get caught.

372
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:54,233
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

373
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:55,100
[FOLDER THUDS]

374
00:19:55,267 --> 00:19:57,267
Do you think
I don't know that, Jacob?

375
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:01,700
Why don't you ask yourself
why you couldn't find someone

376
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,733
who would fix our
company records?

377
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:06,567
I suggested a lot of names,
but you said no.

378
00:20:06,667 --> 00:20:08,133
You don't trust them.

379
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,467
Fine! I don't!

380
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:15,233
If Mike were here,
he'd know what to do.

381
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:18,433
But he's gone. He took our money
and killed himself.

382
00:20:18,533 --> 00:20:22,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

383
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,300
The old man will surely
get mad at me again.

384
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:27,300
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

385
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:33,133
Uh... Excuse me, sirs.

386
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:35,967
Is there a problem?

387
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:40,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

388
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:45,333
I heard that the NRA
is subjecting us to an audit.

389
00:20:47,533 --> 00:20:51,333
Is that what this is about?
Are those the company books?

390
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:56,367
Sir, taxes is one of my
areas of expertise.

391
00:20:56,533 --> 00:20:58,200
I can help you.

392
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:00,467
Get out, Trinidad.

393
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:12,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

394
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:22,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

395
00:21:39,767 --> 00:21:46,800
[TENSE MUSIC BUILDING]

396
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:03,400
Handling taxes
is one of my expertise.

397
00:22:03,533 --> 00:22:04,600
I can protect you.

398
00:22:04,733 --> 00:22:06,267
You created
the problem

399
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,267
so you could be
the one to fix it?

400
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:09,433
A criminal mind.

401
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:10,867
I'll support you too.

402
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:13,067
A complete beast
in skill...

403
00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:16,333
I've discovered
a lot of unexplained permits.

404
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:17,800
What do you want?

405
00:22:17,933 --> 00:22:18,967
I've got them cornered.

406
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:21,233
I think I can infiltrate
their group.

407
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:23,800
I need you to do
something for me.

408
00:22:24,767 --> 00:22:26,133
How well do you
know your dad?

409
00:22:26,267 --> 00:22:27,433
What kind of
question is that?

410
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:29,233
- Where are you going?
- Are you my boyfriend?

411
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:30,733
I can take care
of myself, Enzo.

412
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:33,567
The silence is
going to break.

413
00:22:33,667 --> 00:22:36,233
- Are you okay?
- Good thing I didn't get hurt.

414
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,767
I made a new friend,

415
00:22:37,933 --> 00:22:38,900
King!

416
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,567
Get ready for
a new kind of scam...

417
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:43,133
Who didn't hit
the quota?!

418
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:44,400
Have mercy, sir!

419
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:45,867
[CRYING, COUGHING]

420
00:22:45,967 --> 00:22:47,867
New characters...

421
00:22:47,967 --> 00:22:50,033
You sure are hackers
and programmers.

422
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:52,633
You can't fix the mess
your father made!

423
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,000
Back to work!

424
00:22:55,467 --> 00:22:56,800
Hallelujah!

425
00:22:56,967 --> 00:22:58,267
- Yes!
- That's it!

426
00:22:59,967 --> 00:23:01,500
I'm the one
replying to you.

427
00:23:01,633 --> 00:23:02,600
I'm Rainier.

428
00:23:03,433 --> 00:23:04,667
I'll come see you.

429
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:08,933
...for a more exciting fight.
